{"lemma":"ذُبابٌ","slug":"ذُبابٌ","root":"ذ.ب.ب","root_slug":"ذ-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ذُباب","root":"ذبب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13655","n13658"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8F%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"flies, fly (insect)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pupil (of the eye)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"point (of a sword)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ذ ب ب (ḏ b b), from Proto-Semitic *ḏubab-, from Proto-Afroasiatic *ðuṗṗ. Cognate with Akkadian 𒉏 (zubbum) and Hebrew זְבוּב (zəbūb) and Amharic ዝምብ (zəmb)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13655","headword_ar":"ذُبَابٌ","root":"*b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"common fly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black thing that is in houses, that falls into the vessel and into food;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) so called, accord. to Ed-Demeeree, because of its fluttering about, or because it returns as often as it is driven away: (TA:) and likewise applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) which is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbu Algayovi","text_ar":"ذُبَابُ الغَيْثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fly of the rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (IAth, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbu gayovK","text_ar":"ذُبَابُ غَيْثٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the fly of rain"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because the rain is the means of producing herbage, and by herbage it is fed; (Mgh;) or because it accompanies rain, and lives upon that which the rain causes to grow: (IAth, TA:) [accord. to some, it is a coll. gen. n.; and] the n. un. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbapN","text_ar":"ذُبَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, K:) one should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ib~aAnapN","text_ar":"ذِبَّانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as the vulgar do in the present day]: (S:) or one should not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbapN","text_ar":"ذُبَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", though El-Ahmar and Ks are related to have used this word [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of fly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a sing. [properly speaking], and is used as such in the Kur xxii. 72: (M:) the pl. (of pauc., S, Msb) is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*ib~ahN","text_ar":"اَذِبَّهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (of mult., S, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ib~aAnN","text_ar":"ذِبَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ub~N","text_ar":"ذُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) the last mentioned by Sb, accord. to the dial. of Temeem. (M.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laA^awohaY mina Al*~ubaAbi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَاَوْهَى مِنَ الذُّبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is more frail than the fly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^ahowanu EalaY~a mino Taniyni","text_ar":"هُوَ اَهْوَنُ عَلَىَّ مِنْ طَنِينِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~ubaAbi","text_ar":"الذُّبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is more contemptible to me than the buzzing of the fly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manojaY Al*~ubaAbi","text_ar":"مَنْجَى الذُّبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The refuge of the fly"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov., applied to him who is protected by his ignobleness. (Har p. 332: there written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manojaA","text_ar":"مَنْجَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in two places,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnjA^","text_ar":"منجا"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Al*~ubaAbi","text_ar":"اَبُو الذُّبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The father of the fly"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an appellation used as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He who has stinking breath;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Al*~ib~aAni","text_ar":"اَبُو الذِّبَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the father of the flies"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, TA:) and is especially applied to 'Abd-El-Melik Ibn-Marwán: (M, A, TA:) whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboxaru mino A^abiY Al*~ubaAbi","text_ar":"اَبْخَرُ مِنْ اَبِى الذُّبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abiY Al*~ib~aAni","text_ar":"اَبِى الذِّبَّانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More stinking in breath than Abu-dh-Dhubáb"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abu-dh-Dhibbán"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"annoyance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"harm;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbaniY *ubaAbN","text_ar":"اَصَابَنِى ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil, &c., befell me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (A;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAba fulaAnFA mino","text_ar":"اَصَابَ فُلَانًا مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnK *ubaAbN laA*iEN","text_ar":"فُلَانٍ ذُبَابٌ لَاذِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a hurting fly"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell upon such a one from such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continual evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAbaka *ubaAbN","text_ar":"اَصَابَكَ ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino h`*aA AlA^amori","text_ar":"مِنْ هٰذَا الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Continual evil hath befallen thee from this thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~uhaA *ubaAbN","text_ar":"شَرُّهَا ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Her,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"their, evil is a continual evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ill luck."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K.) Fr relates that the Prophet saw a man with long hair; and said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)  This is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ill luck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN *ubaAbiY~N","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ ذُبَابِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An unlucky man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (T.) ―         -b4-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Plague,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pestilence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Diabolical possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insanity."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ignorance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN maHo$iY~N Al*~ubaAbi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ مَحْشِىٌّ الذُّبَابِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man stuffed with ignorance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.) ―         -b7-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inosaAn","text_ar":"اـِنْسَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pupil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apple,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the eye: (AZ, T, S, M, A, K:) so in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^aEaz~u EalaY~a mino","text_ar":"هُوَ اَعَزُّ عَلَىَّ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbi AlEayoni","text_ar":"ذُبَابِ العَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is dearer to me than the apple of the eye"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A:) [ISd says,] I think it to be so termed as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAb","text_ar":"ذُبَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly so called; i.e. the fly]. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~ubaAbu","text_ar":"الذُّبَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A black speck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spot, in the interior of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hadaqap","text_ar":"حَدَقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dark part"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the eye of the horse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.) The pl. is as above. (M.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbu Als~ayofi","text_ar":"ذُبَابُ السَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbapN","text_ar":"ذُبَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ayofi","text_ar":"السَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taraf","text_ar":"طَرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) [each app. here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"though the former also means the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sword,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the part wherewith one strikes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its extremity with which one is pierced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transpierced;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning edge] with which one strikes is called its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraAr","text_ar":"غِرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":": (En-Nadr, T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its tapering,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pointed, extremity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"expl. by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tarafuhu AlmutaTar~ifu","text_ar":"طَرَفُهُ المُتَطَرِّفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the point"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of its extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is between its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aforataAni","text_ar":"شَفْرَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) the parts of its two edges that are on either side of it are its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZubataAni","text_ar":"ظُبَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": the ridge in the middle of it, on the inner and outer sides, is called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayor","text_ar":"عَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and each has what are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraAraAni","text_ar":"غِرَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which are the part between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eayor","text_ar":"عَيْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"and each one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZubataAni","text_ar":"ظُبَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the outer side of the sword and the corresponding portion of the inner side, each of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"giraAraAni","text_ar":"غِرَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being on the inner side of the sword and its outer side. (AZ, T, TA.) [The swords of the Arabs, in the older times, were generally straight, twoedged, and tapering to a point; and so are many of them in the present day; a little wider towards the point than towards the hilt.] Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vamarapu Als~awoTi yatobaEuhaA *ubaAbu Als~ayofi","text_ar":"ثَمَرَةُ السَّوْطِ يَتْبَعُهَا ذُبَابُ السَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The knot,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tail, at the end of the whip is followed by the point of the sword;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., whipping (if it effect not the desired correction) is followed by slaughter]. (A.) ―         -b9-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ubaAbN","text_ar":"ذُبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies likewise (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~","text_ar":"حَدّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extremity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edge,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of anything. (A 'Obeyd, T.) ―         -b10-  (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pointed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp, part of the extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the ear (A 'Obeyd, M, K) of a horse (A 'Obeyd, M) and of a man. (M.) ―         -b11-  (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharp edge"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the teeth of camels. (S, TA.) ―         -b12-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that first comes forth of the flower"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hin~aA='","text_ar":"حِنَّا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","IAth","Msb","M","A","T","AZ"]},{"entry_id":"n13658","headword_ar":"ذَبَّابٌ","root":"*b","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who repels from,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defends, with energy, his wife,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wives,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mi*ab~N","text_ar":"مِذَبٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yiwomN *ab~aAbN","text_ar":"يِوْمٌ ذَبَّابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sultry day in which the wild animals are infested by numerous gnats, and drive them away with their tails:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the act being thus attributed to the day. (A.)       -A2-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}